specify_cell_stack_group(25.10)                specify_cell_stack_group(25.10)

Name
       specify_cell_stack_group - Defines the stack rule of a cell group

Syntax
       specify_cell_stack_group

       [-help]

       -name <group_name>

       {-max_horizontal_length <max_continuous_length> }

       Defines the stack rule of a cell group.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each specify_cell_stack_group parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man specify_cell_stack_group

       -max_horizontal_length <max_continuous_length>
              Specifies the maximum continuous length in horizontal direction.

       -name <group_name>
              Specifies the cell group name with the stack constraint.

